{
  "texts": [
    "Microstructure analysis SF(SF) improves the microstructural properties of concrete by enhancing the transition zone.",
    "Sadrmomtazi et al. [42] found that SF increases density and reduces crystallization, leading to lower permeability and better durability.",
    "This enhancement improves the interface transition zone (ITZ), resulting in superior mechanical performance and durability as per Qureshi et al. [48].",
    "According to Ali et al. [44], SF creates a denser microstructure with stronger aggregate-cement matrix bonds.",
    "Wang et al. [45] similarly reported that SF promotes a more uniform cement matrix with better particle distribution."
  ]
}